column5: We will be doing a day trip,end of May, on Lac Seul, with Dave as our guide. Has any one been at the lodge to stay, and fish there?
We will be doing a day trip,end of May, on Lac Seul, with Dave as our guide. Has any one been at the lodge to stay, and fish there?
White Wing is a very nice resort. It has good accomodations. If you intend on being there for the day, make certain to stay for dinner. They have an excellent menu.....top notch food.

Do an Advanced Search for "White Wing Lodge" there are about 50 posts mentioning WWL. :cheers:
Thank for the info Opichii and JDP.We allway wanted to try the great Lac Suel, been fishing out of Tallpine camp for 17 years.

We did the day trip on May 28 out of Whitewing resort....started out slow but found the eye's in 2-7 fow, wow....so much bigger is size compare to what we are use to.....had 5 of us in two boat with Ron as our guide...will do it again next year.....the water level was 7 feet low, with the rain coming it should go up....
